title: Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex girls tennis tournament results (BRACKETS)
text:
Fran Varela-Seri advanced to the finals of the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex tournament. (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 08, 2015 2:02 AM, updated October 08, 2015 2:23 AM 
The Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex girls tennis tournament wrapped up last week. 
Hunterdon Central won the crown by sweeping the championships in each bracket. 
North Hunterdon finished second as the Lions advanced to finals in three positions. Kiera Horun made the finals in No. 3 singles, Catrina Gutescu and Hannah Trinity at first doubles and Amanda Ferrante and Juliette Shore at No. 2 doubles. 
Phillipsburg was in third place in the team standings as the Stateliners had two players earn second-place finishes. Fran Varela-Seri reached the finals at No. 1 singles and Jessica Minardi finished second at No. 2 singles.
